          _t_i_m_s_e_r_v_e_r listens at a well-known UDP port ("time" or
          "timserver", 37/udp) for requests to provide the standard
          Internet machine readable time service.  A single datagram
          containing 4 bytes is sent back to the requester,
          representing an integer in network byte order containing of
          the number of seconds since midnight, January 1, 1900.  This
          service is normally provided under 4.3BSD by an internal
          service in _i_n_e_t_d(8C), and is included here only for those
          systems not having that program.  This service is used by an
          Annex terminal server to sync its internal clock to the
          correct time.

